name: Green Gadjah Ubud Bali
address: Jalan Agung Mas Jl. Raya Br Sema No.8, Melinggih, Kec. Payangan, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80572, Indonesia
review 1:
Great place for all the family. Beautiful waterfall, a nice pool to swim in and a well set-up dog park and nature walk.

We also had a meal at the pool cafe, it was the best Ayam sambal we have had in Bali and the prices are cheaper than anywhere else we have seen too (55k for each meal).

Worth the 50k entry for international tourists.

Very quiet at the moment due to low season, so good time to visit. The staff are doing small upgrades to the park but it is very clean, tidy and well maintained

Staff are all lovely and friendly too.

Terima Kasih!
review 2:
After reading the notes from the owner, we thought we would try green gadjah.
Disappointed is the best thing to say. The place is full of potential but we couldn't understand why we were the only ones there. We met our friends who had already arrived. We were told at the gate we had to pay 50k each entrance fee. This is a lot in bali terms. We said we are just meeting friends for lunch. They said it covers the pool and a free drink. Yet we only wanted to eat. The free drink is a tiny bottle of water.
When we got in, we saw our friends with no one else in the venue. I asked them where everyone, and they replied its the high entrance fee that put people off."
The food was average, but only a third of it was available, such as nasi and pizza.
How to kill what could be a great spot for locals a d tourist. We live in bali so we see many places. This is by far the worst managed place I've seen. Take a look at the video and pictures. I think k you can make up your own minds.
review 3: Nice waterfall site easily accessible unlike other waterfalls. Pool, cafe/resto is also on site. Only $3 entrance fee to go all the way down to the waterfall.
review 4: Great Dog friendly attraction in Ubud the walk is well laid out with plenty of rest areas the river and waterfall are very unique with landing platforms for photographs from different angles ,the area has a play area for the dogs and the two resident dogs are very welcoming and friendly JoJo the golden retriever and jedi the gorgi, we enjoyed our lunch of fish and chips and nasi goreng special with some very nice passion fruit drinks ,all the staff were super friendly , there is a nice swimming pool that over looks the jungle canopy,and a kids play area ,we will definitely be back
review 5: place is very big. nice food. there is a dog park with three adorable dogs. recommended for nature and dog lovers.

name: Villa Kelusa
address: Dusun Banjar Ayah, Kelusa, Kec. Payangan, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80572, Indonesia
review 1:
As a Wedding planner & Stylist, Villa Kelusa is one of the best location I could recommend to host a special event! Thank you to Nopi from Lotus Management for your impeccable communication and remote help with the details...
Thank you to Pak Wayan, the Manager of Villa Kelusa, for your incredible assistance during the wedding celebration days, and for leading your beautiful team. Wayan is truly dedicated to make the best experience for his guests while giving such care to his team and the Villa itself. His incredible smile, kindness and willingness really made the experience of organising an event there so much easier! Thank you on behalf of Ashmi, Joel (and me dearly) for helping us create the dream day, as a true team and family, for everyone! I would recommend Villa Kelusa and Kelusa family to all my future clients for their Ubud wedding :)
review 2: Beautiful villa surrounded by rice paddies. Lovely place to have  intimate wedding as that's why I was there. Lovely place and lovely staff. The view is fantastic. The room where the bride getting ready etc it's very nice on the second floor where you can see everything. The pool is medium size but it's infinity and right next to rice paddies. Lovely spot for honeymooners too. Parking not that big tho. But enough .
review 3: Lovely staff and perfect villa in Ubud. The villa is clean. The best thing is the amazing swimming pool with the view
review 4: It's a perfect villa to escape. Great for family holiday
review 5: The villa has magnificent view. Love this place. Definitely will come again

name: Kelusa Village Experience
address: Jl. Yudistira No.3, Kelusa, Kec. Payangan, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80572, Indonesia
review 1:
It is tourist friendly village. Hotels, villas and home stays are availlable. Some choices are available for low budget tourists or backpackers. They could rent the villagers' houses.
The thing is that the bridge through the village is really narrow. It is only enough for a car. Make sure you take a stop before passing trhrough the bridge.
review 2: A great local experience but not too much to do, it can be a stop along the way. There are ample of dogs so don't stop here if you're afraid of dogs.
review 3: Keluasa is located in gianyar, it's 30 km from denpasar. It's a Nice village with perfect weather and nice view, you can fine the humble and friendly people in this village. the special tradition that only has in kelusa village is "tabuh rah" in hyang api temple. It held in kuningan day
review 4: Humble village..experience with many activities like a village cycling,wild trek,nature trekking and traditional activities like a balinese dance,music,making offering,traditional flowing and so many haritage tradition..
review 5: kelusa village is the one village in gianyar regency only 20 minute from ubud centre.Kelusa village they famous with the nature,tradition and special for jungle trekking

name: Authentic House Kelusa
address: H753+4Q9, Keliki, Tegallalang, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80572, Indonesia
review 1: A great place in beautiful surroundings and what's more in the authentic village of Kelusa. The family is just wonderful, amazingly hospitable, Desa the hostess a very inspired cook, who serves the most delicious meals from ingredients growing in the family garden. Dewa the host is a wonderful man ready to share with you, if you are interested, his vast knowledge of Balinese traditions and culture. And he is great guide for discovering the authentic Bali, traveling by car, motorbike, and  on foot through the rice paddies that start from the house.  What Dewa doesn't know about Bali isn't worth knowing. Fantastic adventure. Top value for money.
review 2: Great place to experience How Bali looked like decades ago. Warmly recommend to spend time with Dewa and his family. We will return!
review 3:
I stayed only one night in this place that I found through a friend and I was really amazed about the simple beauty of the place, the warm welcome and the great food home made.
I recommend to anyone who want to have something different from the touristic bali part.
